@startuml MagicLinkSSO-Flow

title Magic Link SSO Authentication Flow (Site + Scope Aware)

actor User
participant "Client App\n(Angular / Fastify /\nNext.js / Nuxt / Django)" as Client
participant "SSO Server" as SSO
participant "Email Server" as Email
collections "Token Service\n(verification JWT signing,\naccess JWT signing,\n+ used-token replay cache)" as TokenService

== Redirect Flow ==

User -> Client: Access Protected Page (/protected)
Client -> Client: Check auth cookie
alt Cookie exists and is valid
    Client -> User: Render protected content
else Cookie missing or invalid
    Client -> User: Redirect to SSO /signin\n?returnUrl=...&verifyUrl=...&scope=...
    User -> SSO: Open /signin
    SSO -> User: Render hosted sign-in page
    User -> SSO: Submit email address\n(scope is optional app-provided context)
    SSO -> SSO: Resolve site from returnUrl/verifyUrl\nand authorize email + requested scope
    SSO -> TokenService: Sign verification token\n(JWT + iss + aud(siteId) + scope + jti)
    SSO -> Email: Send magic link to configured verifyUrl?token=...
    Email --> User: Receive magic link email

    User -> Email: Click magic link
    Email -> User: Open client /verify-email?token=...
    User -> Client: GET /verify-email?token=...
    Client -> SSO: GET /verify-email?token=...\n(Accept: application/json,\nX-Magic-SSO-Preview-Secret)
    SSO -> TokenService: Verify signature, expiry, iss, aud(siteId),\ntrusted returnUrl, and scope without consuming the token
    SSO --> Client: 200 JSON { email }
    Client -> User: Render no-store confirmation page\n(preview token is not consumed)
    Client -> SSO: POST /verify-email { token } (Accept: application/json)
    SSO -> TokenService: Verify signature, expiry, iss, aud(siteId),\ntrusted returnUrl, scope, and one-time use
    SSO --> Client: 200 JSON { accessToken(email, scope) }
    Client -> Client: Verify access token\n(expected iss + aud + signature)\nand set auth cookie
    Client -> User: Redirect to protected page
end

== API Flow ==

User -> Client: Access Protected Page (/protected)
Client -> Client: Check auth cookie
alt Cookie exists and is valid
    Client -> User: Render protected content
else Cookie missing or invalid
    Client -> User: Render local login UI
    User -> Client: Submit email address
    Client -> SSO: POST /signin { email, returnUrl, verifyUrl, scope? }
    SSO -> SSO: Resolve site from returnUrl/verifyUrl\nand authorize email + requested scope
    SSO -> TokenService: Sign verification token\n(JWT + iss + aud(siteId) + scope + jti)
    SSO -> Email: Send magic link to configured verifyUrl?token=...
    Email --> User: Receive magic link email

    User -> Email: Click magic link
    Email -> User: Open client /verify-email?token=...
    User -> Client: GET /verify-email?token=...
    Client -> SSO: GET /verify-email?token=...\n(Accept: application/json,\nX-Magic-SSO-Preview-Secret)
    SSO -> TokenService: Verify signature, expiry, iss, aud(siteId),\ntrusted returnUrl, and scope without consuming the token
    SSO --> Client: 200 JSON { email }
    Client -> User: Render no-store confirmation page\n(preview token is not consumed)
    Client -> SSO: POST /verify-email { token } (Accept: application/json)
    SSO -> TokenService: Verify signature, expiry, iss, aud(siteId),\ntrusted returnUrl, scope, and one-time use
    SSO --> Client: 200 JSON { accessToken(email, scope) }
    Client -> Client: Verify access token\n(expected iss + aud + signature)\nand set auth cookie
    Client -> User: Redirect to protected page
end

== Server-Managed Verify Flow ==

User -> SSO: GET /verify-email?token=...
SSO -> TokenService: Verify signature, expiry, iss, aud(siteId),\ntrusted returnUrl, and scope without consuming the token
SSO -> User: Render no-store confirmation page\nset temporary HttpOnly token cookie + CSRF cookie\nand remove token from URL
User -> SSO: POST /verify-email\n(CSRF form token)
SSO -> TokenService: Verify signature, expiry, iss, aud(siteId),\ntrusted returnUrl, scope, and one-time use
SSO -> SSO: Clear temporary token cookie\nand set server auth cookie
SSO -> User: Redirect to trusted returnUrl

@enduml
